  "prompt": "What is the definition of current?",
  "response": "Current is the rate of flow of electric charge through a conductor, typically measured in amperes (A). More specifically:\n\n1. In electrical terms, current is the movement of electric charges (usually electrons) through a conductive material.\n\n2. The standard unit of current is the ampere, which represents one coulomb of charge passing a point in one second.\n\n3. Current can flow in different directions, such as direct current (DC) which flows in one constant direction, or alternating current (AC) which periodically changes direction.\n\n4. In physics, current is calculated by the equation I = Q/t, where I is current, Q is the amount of charge, and t is the time.\n\n5. Current is a fundamental concept in electricity and electronics, describing the flow of electrical energy through a circuit.",
